cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.NE 

This paper is about automatic evaluation of machine translation output without reference, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a novel bidirectional transformer model for feature extraction, which involves deep learning techniques, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) likely sub-categories as well. Additionally, the paper uses real-valued measurements of possible erroneous tokens, which could involve computer vision techniques, making cs.CV (Computer Vision) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper uses a predictive model for quality evaluation, which could involve neural networks, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) a possible sub-category.
